        "id": 1002106
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-01T01:14:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "stopVM still assumes a browser-created NbdServer exists.\n\nIf the BMC reports a proxy device as inserted after a refresh, reconnect, or another UI session, the Stop button is enabled and clicking it throws Cannot read properties of undefined/null (reading \u0027stop\u0027).\n\nRecommendation: only enable browser-proxy Stop when dev.nbd exists, or make stopVM defensive and present an explanatory state for active media that cannot be stopped by the current browser session. If there is a Redfish eject path for this state, use that instead.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 200,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 202,
        "endChar": 6
      },
      "revId": "287f1cabff081e56d97c817e6a867b5fbf0ed2a3",
