      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-12T13:32:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Fixed. Both parts of the recommendation are addressed:\n\n1. The browser-proxy Stop button now uses v-if\u003d\"dev.isActive \u0026\u0026 dev.nbd\" —\n   it is only rendered when the current browser session owns the NBD\n   connection, preventing the crash entirely.\n\n2. When isActive\u003dtrue and nbd\u003dnull (device reported as Inserted by the BMC\n   but no browser-owned connection exists — e.g. another UI session or a\n   BMC that retains Inserted state), the card now shows an informational\n   label \"Active in another session\" and a separate Stop button that calls\n   the Redfish EjectMedia action (unmountImage) to eject the media cleanly.\n   stopVM() also has a defensive early-return guard as a belt-and-suspenders\n   measure.\n\nNote: the specific BMC used for testing returns Inserted: false while a\nWebSocket session is active, so the isActive \u0026\u0026 !nbd path is not triggered\nin that environment. However the fix is correct and necessary for BMC\nimplementations that do return Inserted: true, which is the case the\nreviewer encountered during testing.",
      "parentUuid": "38323abc_d1f85183",
